lead_paragraph: Two young California condors were freed today, a milestone in a $25 million effort to save the giant vultures from extinction by breeding them in zoos and returning them to the wild. A male California condor named Chocuyens (Cho-KOO-yens), a female named Xewe (pronounced GAY-wee) and two Andean condors who will keep them company, all stepped onto an open platform today. Neither of the California condors flew immediately but one of the Andean condors did.

headline.main: FOUR RARE CONDORS FREED IN THE WILD
